   <item>
    <widget class="QLabel" name="instructionsLabel">
     <property name="text">
      <string>Instructions:
1. Load your volume (NIfTI format recommended)
2. Create seed points: Use "Reset Seeds" for automatic placement or manually create two fiducial points
3. Set radius estimate in image units (mm or cm - default: mm)
4. Configure nnUNet settings:
   - Click "Download Pretrained Weights" for automatic model download (236 MB)
   - Or set custom nnUNet results path to trained models
5. Set output directory for results
6. Click "Run SeqSeg"
7. Use visualization buttons to load results:
   - "Load Latest Segmentation" - loads .mha segmentation as overlay
   - "Load Latest Surface Mesh" - loads .vtp 3D surface model
   - "Browse All Outputs" - view and load all output files

Features:
- Automatic dependency installation (SeqSeg, nnUNet, etc.)
- Apple Silicon (M1/M2) Mac compatibility
- Automatic seed point placement within volume bounds
- Output files saved to: output_directory/output/
- First run may take longer due to model and dependency setup</string>
     </property>
     <property name="wordWrap">
      <bool>true</bool>
     </property>
     <property name="alignment">
      <set>Qt::AlignLeading|Qt::AlignLeft|Qt::AlignTop</set>
     </property>
    </widget>
